“God, who knows me by name, [is] right next to me.” 
― Shirley Corder, #StrengthRenewed #Inspiration #cancer

“All the seeming "coincidences" .... were actually God catching me in his arms.” 
― Shirley Corder, #StrengthRenewed #inspiration #cancer

“The luxury of relaxation ... is part of the healing process.” 
― Shirley Corder, #StrengthRenewed #inspiration #cancer

“Help me to get my eyes off my suffering and onto you, God.” 
― Shirley Corder, #StrengthRenewed #inspiration #cancer

“Nothing takes God by surprise, not even cancer.” 
― Shirley Corder, #StrengthRenewed:
“God promises to hear and answer our prayers, but he doesn't always answer the way we want him to.” #StrengthRenewed #Inspiration #cancer

“It's okay to be afraid. God is not disappointed by your fear.” 
― Shirley Corder, #StrengthRenewed #inspiration #cancer

“#Cancer may have blindsided you, but it didn't blindside God." #StrengthRenewed #inspiration 
― Shirley Corder

“Please don’t tell me you know just how I feel--you don't.” 
― Shirley Corder, #Strength Renewed:

“There's only one way to become an eagle, and that's to be born an eagle.” 
― Shirley Corder, #StrengthRenewed #inspiration #cancer
“Lord, thank you for the people who care more about me than about their schedules.” #Strength Renewed #inspirational
